The case of businessman Duduzane Zuma, at the Randburg Magistrate’s Court, has been postponed to 23rd of August 2018. Former President Jacob Zuma’s son is facing two charges of culpable homicide following a crash in 2014 on the M1 highway in Johannesburg. Phumzile Dube was killed after Zuma’s Porsche collided with the taxi in which she was travelling. Her fellow passenger Nanki Mashaba‚ who was also injured in the crash‚ died in hospital a few weeks later.  